# Naming Conventions

Full standard: [docs/agent/standards/common/naming.md](../../docs/agent/standards/common/naming.md)

## Files
- Services: `JobsService.ts`, `AuthService.ts` (PascalCase + `Service`)
- Controllers: `JobsController.ts` (PascalCase + `Controller`)
- Modules: `jobs.module.ts` (kebab-case + `.module.ts`)
- DTOs: `CreateJobDto.ts`, `UpdateJobDto.ts`, `JobSearchDto.ts`
- Types: `types.ts` per domain (never `interfaces.ts`)
- Barrels: always `index.ts`

## Symbols
- Classes: `PascalCase` (`JobsService`, `CreateJobDto`)
- Interfaces: `IPascalCase` for adapter contracts (`IJwtStrategy`); plain `PascalCase` for data shapes
- Enums: `PascalCase` (`JobStatus`, `ApplicationStatus`)
- Enum values: `UPPER_SNAKE` (`JobStatus.ACTIVE`, `ApplicationStatus.NEW`)
- Constants/tokens: `UPPER_SNAKE` (`JWT_SECRET`, `JOB_REPOSITORY`)
- Methods/properties: `camelCase`
- Route paths: `kebab-case` (`/warehouse-jobs`, `/quick-apply`)
- Database columns: `snake_case` (Prisma maps to `camelCase` in TypeScript)

## Domain-Specific Naming
- Job posting: `PostedBy`, `CompanyPackageId`, `SourceType`
- Application states: match `ApplicationStatus` enum exactly
- Batch: `batchId`, `BatchJobItem`, `BatchStatus`
